.TH "ELSERENO" "1" "2026\-04\-25" "ElSereno user commands" "Commands"
.SH NAME
\f[B]elsereno\f[R] \(em ICS/OT and legacy\-network exposure auditor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]elsereno\f[R] [\f[B]\-\-config\f[R] \f[I]file\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-\-dry\-run\f[R]] [\f[B]\-\-format\f[R] \f[I]fmt\f[R]]
\f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]args\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]ElSereno\f[R] scans for and audits exposure of legacy + ICS / OT
network protocols (Modbus, S7, EtherNet/IP, BACnet, DNP3, IEC
60870\-5\-104, HART\-IP, Niagara Fox, OPC UA, ATG, XOT, AT modems,
banner / dictionary, plus PBX SIP / IAX2 / pbxhttp / TR\-069 CWMP).
Two binaries ship from the same module:
.TP
\f[B]elsereno\f[R]
Default (read\-only) build.
Scan, fingerprint, score, triage, serve dashboard.
Writes refused at the wire layer.
.TP
\f[B]elsereno\-offensive\f[R]
\f[CR]\-tags offensive\f[R] build.
Adds \f[B]dial\f[R], \f[B]exploit\f[R], \f[B]harvest\f[R], \f[B]proxy
listen\f[R] (write\-gated), and \f[B]write\f[R] subcommands.
Every mutating call clears the triple\-confirm wrapper (ADR\-039) \(em
\f[CR]\-\-accept\-writes\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-confirm\-target\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-confirm\-token\f[R].
.SH COMMANDS
The default\-build subcommand list is below.
Run \f[CR]elsereno *command* \-\-help\f[R] for per\-command flags.
.TP
\f[B]api\f[R]
HTTP API meta\-operations.
\f[CR]api openapi\f[R] prints the live OpenAPI 3.1 spec.
.TP
\f[B]audit\f[R]
Audit\-log operations: \f[B]show\f[R], \f[B]verify\-file\f[R],
\f[B]import\f[R], \f[B]rebase\f[R], \f[B]purge\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]backup\f[R]
Encrypted backup + restore (vault\-keyed AES\-256\-GCM).
.TP
\f[B]completion\f[R]
Generate shell completions (placeholder; see \f[CR]\-\-help\f[R] until
cobra\(cqs generator is wired).
.TP
\f[B]config\f[R]
Inspect and validate configuration.
Subcommands include \f[B]show\f[R], \f[B]lint\f[R], \f[B]fmt\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]creds\f[R]
Manage stored credentials inside the vault.
.TP
\f[B]db\f[R]
Database operations: \f[B]migrate up/down\f[R], \f[B]status\f[R],
\f[B]verify\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]doctor\f[R]
Run cross\-platform preflight checks (Go runtime, capabilities, nmap,
IPv6, DNS, disk).
.TP
\f[B]explain\f[R]
Explain how a finding\(cqs score was computed (ADR\-006 factors).
.TP
\f[B]fmt\f[R]
Re\-emit a YAML config with canonical formatting.
.TP
\f[B]gen\-man\f[R]
Generate man1 pages via cobra/doc (placeholder; current man1 lives under
\f[CR]man/src/man1/*.md\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]legal\f[R]
Print the acceptable\-use policy disclaimer.
.TP
\f[B]lint\f[R]
Validate \f[B]elsereno.yaml\f[R] and optional \f[B]scope.yaml\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]plugins\f[R]
Manage protocol plugins.
\f[B]plugins list\f[R] prints the compiled\-in set (17 in the v1.12
default build).
.TP
\f[B]proxy\f[R]
Protocol\-aware interception proxy.
\f[B]proxy listen\f[R] runs a write\-gated proxy in the offensive build
(read\-only fail\- closed in default).
.TP
\f[B]scan\f[R]
Scan a set of targets and emit findings.
\f[CR]\-\-input <provider>:<query>\f[R] accepts \f[CR]list:\f[R],
\f[CR]nmap:\f[R], \f[CR]stdin\f[R], \f[CR]shodan:\f[R],
\f[CR]censys:\f[R], \f[CR]fofa:\f[R], \f[CR]zoomeye:\f[R],
\f[CR]onyphe:\f[R], \f[CR]internetdb:\f[R].
The first 5 require \f[CR]\-\-api\-creds\-file <0600.yaml>\f[R];
\f[B]internetdb\f[R] is no\-key.
.TP
\f[B]scoring\f[R]
Inspect the scoring weights and severity thresholds.
.TP
\f[B]serve\f[R]
Start the HTTP dashboard at the configured listen address + serve
\f[CR]/api/v1\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]triage\f[R]
Group NDJSON findings into quick\-win / strategic / routine.
.TP
\f[B]vault\f[R]
Manage the encrypted credential vault.
\f[B]vault init\f[R], \f[B]unlock\f[R], \f[B]lock\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]version\f[R]
Print binary version, commit, and build date.
.TP
\f[B]why\f[R]
Explain the scoring posture for a target.
.SH OFFENSIVE\-ONLY COMMANDS
The \f[CR]\-tags offensive\f[R] build adds:
.TP
\f[B]dial\f[R]
Dial guard (ADR\-041).
Subcommands: \f[B]validate\f[R] (single number) and \f[B]batch\f[R]
(wardialing batch with \f[CR]\-\-numbers\-file\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]exploit\f[R]
CVE exploit catalogue.
\f[B]exploit list\f[R] + \f[B]exploit dry\-run\f[R]
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[B]exploit run\f[R].
.RE
.TP
\f[B]harvest\f[R]
Credential harvest probes (telnet / ftp / http\-basic / snmp).
.TP
\f[B]write\f[R]
Protocol\-specific write operations.
Per\-protocol subcommands: \f[B]modbus dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]modbus
send\f[R], \f[B]modbus proxy\-dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]sip dry\-run\f[R],
\f[B]iax2 dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]pbxhttp dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]opcua
dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]bacnet dry\-run\f[R], \f[B]cwmp dry\-run\f[R].
.SH WRITE\-GATE FLAGS (offensive build)
The seven write\-gated proxies all share the
\f[CR]\-\-allow\-file <path.yaml>\f[R] round\-trip flow.
Direct CLI flags per proxy:
.TP
\f[B]Modbus\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-function <FC>\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-write unit=N;fc=M;start=A;end=B\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]OPC UA\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-service <TypeID>\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-node\-id ns=N;i=M|s=STR|g=HEX|b=HEX\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-call\-method object=\&...;method=\&...\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]SIP\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-method <NAME>\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-to\-prefix <prefix>\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-aor <AOR>\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-from\-domain <host>\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]IAX2\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-subclass <NAME>\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]pbxhttp\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-allow METHOD:/path\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]BACnet\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-service\-choice <N>\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-object type=N;instance=M;property=P\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]CWMP\f[R]
\f[CR]\-\-rpc <Name>\f[R], \f[CR]\-\-param\-prefix <prefix>\f[R],
\f[CR]\-\-firmware url=\&...;sha256=\&...\f[R].
